The police officer caught singing and dancing to a cult song in a viral Tiktok video, Isaac Mathew, has been demoted from the rank of corporal to constable. Force Public Relations Officer, CSP Olumuyiwa Adejobi, disclosed this in a statement on Sunday. He said the demotion followed the outcome of an orderly room trial of the offender and a review of the recommended punishment for the offences of discreditable conduct, promoting secret cults as well as the violation of the social media policy of Nigeria Police Force.   24 hours to very critical decisions: APC beware     Tambuwal, Deputy pick Sokoto PDP senatorial tickets     Attackers of Owo church came in a bus- Witnesses   Mathew, who was attached to the Ebonyi Police Command, was seen in a viral Tiktok video on May 7 dressed in full police uniform, singing, dancing and brandishing an AK-47 rifle in praise of a secret confraternity. Muyiwa said other disciplinary cases of unprofessional conduct by officers in encounters with members of the public are also being looked into in line with the current police administrationâ€™s goal of ensuring a transparent, accountable, and proactive policing system in Nigeria. According to him, the Inspector General of Police (IGP) Usman Baba, has charged all police officers to uphold professional ethics, discipline, and the ideals of the Force.